    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1a0938-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T22:29:07.349+09:00">As for the wise men, who address themselves to the task of governing the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:03:35.278+09:00">they must certainly know where the disorder arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:07:23.7+09:00">then they are able to govern it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:14:13.007+09:00">then they are not able to govern it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:18:19.838+09:00">Things are the same as with a doctor who wants to cure someone else's disease.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:19:35.181+09:00">He must certainly know where the disease arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:19:48.467+09:00">then he is able to cure it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:20:10.095+09:00">If he does not know where the disease arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:20:21.811+09:00">then he is not able to cure it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:22:01.721+09:00">How, then, should it be any different for those who govern disorder?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:22:38.617+09:00">They must certainly know where the disorder arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:22:44.838+09:00">then they are able to govern it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:22:56.11+09:00">If they do not know where the disorder arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-12T23:23:04.426+09:00">then they are not able to govern it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:46:45.889+09:00">If they do not know where the disorder arises from,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:47:33.582+09:00">As for the wise men, who address themselves to the task of governing the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:50:48.389+09:00">they inevitably have to investigate where the disorder arises from.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:52:32.463+09:00">Let us try to investigate where the disorder arises from.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:54:11.698+09:00">It arises from the fact that people do not care for each other.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:58:30.269+09:00">is something called disorder.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T19:03:49.023+09:00">That subject and son do not serve their ruler or father in piety</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:59:22.341+09:00">Since a son cares for himself and not his father,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T18:59:59.628+09:00">he therefore harms his father and benefits himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T19:01:33.549+09:00">Since a younger brother cares for himself and not his older brother,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T19:01:52.828+09:00">he therefore harms his older brother and benefits himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T19:04:00.311+09:00">Since a subject cares for himself and not his ruler,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="wilke" modified="2019-11-14T19:03:59.192+09:00">he therefore harms his ruler and benefits himself.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
